</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="004F54BAB024350E9122A64AA488EF83" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="type">
<paragraph id="D21AAB0F95584EB9FF76595A996F1FF7" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE8C26DFFB61EF77EBA14F251174DC6C" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
Based on 
<taxonomicName id="ACB7D4B7DE0F4EA405ADE24C4D03CAA7" authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capituliferus subsp. var. var. foliaceus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="capituliferus" subSpecies="var." variety="foliaceus">Convolvulus capituliferus var. foliaceus</taxonomicName>
Verdc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B67025C761C55C93BC483FB6BCF563C4" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="4D4A36696B039E64CD5AB0B058967BED" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="69ECD887ACD01C31280EAFEEBC01B43C" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Leaves and bracts 3-6 cm long giving the inflorescence a leafy appearance. Corolla 9-12 mm long.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B8B1EC618A6F9A3BDE3C61D3ACD26F0D" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EEED039AC813E097D4AED2C7F81D1522" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18C446927C03386758B516E94F0CF293" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
This seems to be the only subspecies in Kenya (
<emphasis id="7DB30AC6D839F2A949A8EEAABF13A4F8" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Gillett</emphasis>
21325, 
<emphasis id="184002CDCB43BD24E7CD9773AE964F03" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Padwa</emphasis>
194) and Ethiopia (
<emphasis id="F97FB7ACCD5CC3683A9C6AD2C12D52F6" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Ellis</emphasis>
232, 
<emphasis id="95686A9B0D08BADBA84D11C188D64ACE" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">de Wilde</emphasis>
5909) but also occurs in Somalia (
<emphasis id="E121957294B7024BC9205D0673D351F8" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Hemming &amp; Deshmukh Jess</emphasis>
298).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="60BAFF60F121EE88B8D946C8F8F579EB" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="notes">
<paragraph id="BE0AC29B567936EB29573CC89E947009" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="469CAF2F409835E9414995EA1A7DF08D" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="2D182753399EBC8E4A50CDB7BFCC45E3" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis id="BAE12E1910BF5AFDE25600F7738C9F7E" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the larger, easily visible, shallowly lobed, blue corolla. 
<bibRefCitation id="0924D2B48AB05935E62F91F4A38EEB0F" author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin (2006</bibRefCitation>
: 235) treated this species as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="3E68E22A12E253F3D9E2CA6E46BFED59" authorityName="Hochst. ex Choisy, Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 9: 405. (Choisy" authorityYear="1845" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus rhyniospermus" order="Solanales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyniospermus">
<emphasis id="DA9C88F6E9CD70E22CB50C808B9A619D" italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Convolvulus rhyniospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<bibRefCitation id="D0816E74AA45098D58EEFB1F13A440DF" author="Verdcourt, B" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="459 - 464" publicationUrl="10.2307/4110047" refId="B375" refString="Verdcourt, B, 1982. Corrections and additions to the &quot;Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V. Kew Bulletin 37: 459 - 464, DOI: 10.2307/4110047" title="Corrections and additions to the &quot; Flora of Tropical East Africa: Convolvulaceae &quot; V." url="10.2307/4110047" volume="37" year="1982">Verdcourt (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 459) drew attention to the distinctive characters of the two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
